(SHOPPING CART PROJECT WORKFLOW) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This document explains the full workflow of the `shopping-cart` project. It is) Tj
T*
(designed for beginners to understand how the app starts, how state is managed, how) Tj
T*
(products are displayed, how discounts are calculated, and how optional Firebase) Tj
T*
(persistence works.) Tj
T*
T*
(---) Tj
T*
T*
(1. APP OVERVIEW) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This is a React shopping cart app built with Vite. Users can:) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ view available products,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ add products to a basket,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ increase or decrease product quantities,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ see discounts applied automatically,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ view subtotal, savings, and total cost.) Tj
T*
T*
(The app also supports optional Firebase Firestore persistence, so the basket can be) Tj
T*
(loaded and saved across page reloads.) Tj
T*
T*
(---) Tj
T*
T*
(2. TECHNOLOGY STACK) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(‚ÄĘ React 19) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Vite) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Redux Toolkit) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Tailwind CSS) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Firebase Firestore \(optional\)) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ Vitest \(unit tests\)) Tj
T*
T*
(---) Tj
T*
T*
(3. PROJECT STRUCTURE) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Important folders and files:) Tj
T*
T*
(‚ÄĘ `src/`) Tj
T*
(  - `main.jsx` ‚ÄĒ app entry point) Tj
T*
(  - `App.jsx` ‚ÄĒ top-level layout and hook usage) Tj
T*
(  - `components/` ‚ÄĒ UI components) Tj
T*
(    - `Products.jsx`) Tj
T*
(    - `ProductItem.jsx`) Tj
T*
(    - `Basket.jsx`) Tj
T*
(    - `BasketItem.jsx`) Tj
T*
(  - `store/` ‚ÄĒ Redux state setup) Tj
T*
(    - `store.js`) Tj
T*
(    - `cartSlice.js`) Tj
T*
(  - `utils/` ‚ÄĒ business logic) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
