(13. BEGINNER TIPS) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(‚ÄĘ `React` renders the UI based on state.) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `Redux` stores the cart in a central place.) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `useEffect\(\)` runs code when components mount or state changes.) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `dispatch\(action\)` tells Redux to update state.) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `calculateBill\(\)` is where the cost calculation lives.) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `Firebase` is optional; the app works without it.) Tj
T*
T*
(If you are new to React, focus first on the components and how they use props and) Tj
T*
(state.) Tj
T*
(If you are new to Redux, focus on `cartSlice.js` and `store.js`.) Tj
T*
T*
(---) Tj
T*
T*
(14. SUMMARY) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This app combines UI, state, pricing rules, and optional cloud persistence.) Tj
T*
(The clean separation of responsibilities makes it easy to understand:) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `components/` build the screen,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `store/` stores the cart,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `utils/` calculates prices,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `firebase/` handles saved data,) Tj
T*
(‚ÄĘ `hooks/` connects sync behavior to React.) Tj
T*
T*
(That is the full workflow from a beginner perspective.) Tj
T*
